==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[ice cream|ice cream]]'' + ''[[cone]]'' (a hollow cone).  Previously [[World's Fair Cornucopia]] [http://www.joyofbaking.com/IceCreamCones.html].

===Alternative spellings===
* [[ice-cream]] cone

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg|ice cream cone}}

# A thin, conical confection baked from [[crepe]] [[batter]], sealed at its apex, used to hold ice cream while it is being eaten.  
# Any sweet, edible cone or half-open cylinder which can be used in this fashion; often made with wafer or waffle techniques.
# An ice cream cone filled with [[ice cream]]. 

====Synonyms====
* [[cone]]
* [[cornet]] (UK), [[ice-cream cornet]]
* [[ice cream]], as in "I'll have an ice cream"
* '' see also [[cornucopia]]''

